  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Trim the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> off the&nbsp;<strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and cut into quarters lengthways</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2-4 tbsp&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, and swirl it around the pan&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>aubergine</strong> and cook for 3 min on each flesh side, until browned</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>browned aubergine</strong> to a baking tray and keep the pan for later&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the aubergine has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;basmati rice</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel, top and tail the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Continue to peel lengths off the carrot until you end up with a pile of <strong>carrot 'ribbons'</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you've peeled as far as you can, grate the inner stem&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated</strong><strong> carrot</strong>, <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5-10 min or until starting to brown and caramelise</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once caramelised, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong> to the carrot mix and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Stir in the <strong>stock</strong> and a large pinch&nbsp;of<strong> sugar</strong>, mixing well to combine</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to low and cook for 5-10 min over a low heat or until thickened - this is your <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>spring onions</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander </strong>roughly, including the stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>carrot ribbons</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong>, <strong>coriander</strong> and<strong> rice vinegar</strong> in a bowl and mix together gently - this is your <strong>salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/305.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
